Title: Lake Trout from Green Lake
Description: Best Lake to fish for lake trout around Seattle area. The best way is still fishing with power bait.

Title: Pacific Sand Dab at Puget Sound
Description: Best place to fish for pacific sand dab is Puget Sound. The best way is bottom fishing with small dead/live bait.

Title: Catching steelhead salmon in Hoh river
Description: Most of the river that enters  the northwest of pacific offers good steelhead salmon. You can catch them by trolling the boat.

Title: How to handle shark if you catch them
Description: The best way is to remove the hook is while the shark is in the water using long-nose pliers or de-hookers. Keep your fingers and tools clear of its gill slots.

Title: Bass fishing near Seattle
Description: The best season to catch largemouth bass will be spring and summer time. You can find largemouth bass almost every lake and river in state of Washington.

Title: Trout in Lake Sammamish
Description: You can catch Cutthroat trout in Lake Sammamish, Washington.

Title: Wedding ring lure to catch rainbow trout
Description: Wedding ring lure are a classic lure and can catch variety of species of fish. It is available in a plethora of sizes, shapes, colors and hook styles.

Title: Seawall project for rockfish and salmon
Description: The old Elliott bay seawall that was built in 1900s, it is preventing salmon from returning back to the river. The people are thinking to replace it will a new seawall that would allow salmon to swim back.

Title: Fly fishing in the fall to catch fish
Description: Fly fishing is another option for fishing in rivers and creeks around seattle..
